Edit->Hide

"Hide" Is used to hide objects in the scene so that only the objects
you are currently working on need to be displayed and manipulated.
This option is very handy to keep object creation speed at its peak.
It is also very useful in placing tightly grouped objects. "Show" will
unhide the hidden objects

"Hide" option contains two sub-choices: "Hide->Selected" will hide all
the currently selected objects. "Hide->Unselected" will hide all
objects not selected. The latter is useful to hide away all objects
that you are not working on.
